\subsection{Comparison-iso typeclass carrier (iter-050)}

The iter-049 transport requires the comparison iso $\mathtt{compIso} : \forall n, \cechCohomology\,C\,F\,\mathcal U\,n \equiv_k \HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,(\bigsqcup_i \mathcal U_i)$ as an \emph{explicit} argument. This forces every call site either to receive the iso as a hypothesis or to construct it from the substantive iter-052+ comparison theorem. Iter-050 packages the iso as a $\Prop$-valued typeclass: existence is wrapped via $\mathtt{Nonempty}$, an extractor recovers it via $\Classical.\mathtt{choice}$, and an instance-driven consumer chains iter-049 with the extractor so that downstream producers (iter-053+) need only provide $[\IsCechAcyclicCover\,F\,\mathcal U]$ and $[\HasCechToHModuleIso\,F\,\mathcal U]$ instances --- the iso passes silently through typeclass synthesis. The $\mathtt{Nonempty}$ wrapper is mandatory: a $\Prop$-valued class field cannot hold the data of a $\LinearEquiv$-valued $\forall n, \ldots$ functional.

\begin{definition}\leanok
[Comparison-iso typeclass carrier, iter-050]
  \label{def:Scheme_HasCechToHModuleIso}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.HasCechToHModuleIso}
  \uses{def:Scheme_cechCohomology, def:Scheme_HModule_prime}
  Let $k$ be a field, $C : \Over\,(\Spec\,(\CommRingCat.\mathtt{of}\,k))$, $F$ a sheaf of $\ModuleCat\,k$ on $\Opens\,C.\mathtt{left}.\mathtt{toTopCat}$, and $\mathcal U : \iota \to \Opens\,C.\mathtt{left}.\mathtt{toTopCat}$. The class $\Scheme.\HasCechToHModuleIso\,F\,\mathcal U$ is a $\Prop$-valued single-field carrier whose field $\mathtt{nonempty\_compIso}$ asserts $\mathtt{Nonempty}\,(\forall n,\ \cechCohomology\,C\,F\,\mathcal U\,n \equiv_k \HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,(\bigsqcup_i \mathcal U_i))$. The iter-052+ comparison theorem will be wrapped via $\langle\langle \mathtt{the\_iso}\rangle\rangle$ to instantiate this class for the $(\toModuleKSheaf\,C, \mathtt{basic\text{-}open\ cover})$ pair.
\end{definition}

\begin{definition}\leanok
[Comparison-iso extractor, iter-050]
  \label{def:Scheme_cechToHModuleIso}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.cechToHModuleIso}
  \uses{def:Scheme_HasCechToHModuleIso}
  Given $[\HasCechToHModuleIso\,F\,\mathcal U]$, the noncomputable function $\Scheme.\cechToHModuleIso$ returns $\forall n,\ \cechCohomology\,C\,F\,\mathcal U\,n \equiv_k \HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,(\bigsqcup_i \mathcal U_i)$ via $\Classical.\mathtt{choice}$ on the class field $\mathtt{nonempty\_compIso}$. Plan-agent $\mathtt{lean\_run\_code}$ probe (iter-050 pass) confirmed kernel-only axioms $[\propext, \Classical.\mathtt{choice}, \Quot.\mathtt{sound}]$; $\Classical.\mathtt{choice}$ was already in the project's kernel-only set since iter-048, so no new axiom is introduced.
\end{definition}

\begin{theorem}\leanok
[Instance-driven top-supremum HModule transport, abstract sheaf form, iter-050]
  \label{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_of_hasCechToHModuleIso_top}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.subsingleton_HModule_of_hasCechToHModuleIso_top}
  \uses{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_of_isCechAcyclicCover_top, def:Scheme_HasCechToHModuleIso, def:Scheme_cechToHModuleIso}
  Same hypotheses as Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_of_isCechAcyclicCover_top}, but the explicit $\mathtt{compIso}$ argument is replaced by a $[\HasCechToHModuleIso\,F\,\mathcal U]$ instance argument: under $[\IsCechAcyclicCover\,F\,\mathcal U]$, $[\HasCechToHModuleIso\,F\,\mathcal U]$, and $\bigsqcup_i \mathcal U_i = \top$, with $n \geq 1$, the type $\HModule\,k\,F\,n$ is a subsingleton.
\end{theorem}

\begin{proof}
\leanok
  Direct application of Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_of_isCechAcyclicCover_top} with the iter-050 extractor $\Scheme.\cechToHModuleIso$ supplied as the explicit comparison iso. The extractor fires automatically on the $[\HasCechToHModuleIso\,F\,\mathcal U]$ instance, recovering the underlying $\forall n, \ldots$ functional that iter-049's consumer expects. Plan-agent $\mathtt{lean\_run\_code}$ probe (iter-050 pass) confirms kernel-only axioms.
\end{proof}

\begin{theorem}\leanok
[Instance-driven top-supremum HModule transport, curve form, iter-050]
  \label{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_of_hasCechToHModuleIso_top_curve}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.subsingleton_HModule_of_hasCechToHModuleIso_top_curve}
  \uses{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_of_hasCechToHModuleIso_top, def:Scheme_toModuleKSheaf}
  Curve specialisation at $F := \Scheme.\toModuleKSheaf\,C$ via the named-argument syntax.
\end{theorem}

\begin{proof}
\leanok
  Direct application of Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_of_hasCechToHModuleIso_top}. Plan-agent $\mathtt{lean\_run\_code}$ probe (iter-050 pass) confirms kernel-only axioms.
\end{proof}

\subsection{Instance-driven supremum HModule\texttt{'} consumer (iter-051)}

The iter-049 / iter-050 instance-driven consumers cover the \emph{top-supremum} case ($\bigsqcup_i \mathcal U_i = \top$, landing on $\HModule\,k\,F\,n$ at universe $u+1$). The iter-053+ producer for $\IsAffineHModuleVanishing\,k\,C\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)$, however, needs the \emph{intermediate-supremum} form: for an affine open $U$ of $C$, pick a basic-open cover $\mathcal U$ with $\bigsqcup_i \mathcal U_i = U$ (\emph{not} $= \top$), and conclude $\Subsingleton\,(\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,i\,U)$ at universe $u$. Iter-048's explicit-argument consumer $\mathtt{subsingleton\_HModule}'\_\mathtt{supr\_of\_isCechAcyclicCover}$ already provides this (Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_prime_supr_of_isCechAcyclicCover}), but it requires the comparison iso as an explicit argument. Iter-051 fills the symmetry gap: a thin instance-driven counterpart that takes $[\HasCechToHModuleIso\,F\,\mathcal U]$ as a typeclass instance instead, so the iter-053+ producer chain consumes both $[\IsCechAcyclicCover]$ and $[\HasCechToHModuleIso]$ uniformly via instance synthesis.

\begin{theorem}\leanok
[Instance-driven supremum HModule\texttt{'} consumer, abstract sheaf form, iter-051]
  \label{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_prime_supr_of_hasCechToHModuleIso}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.subsingleton_HModule'_supr_of_hasCechToHModuleIso}
  \uses{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_prime_supr_of_isCechAcyclicCover, def:Scheme_HasCechToHModuleIso, def:Scheme_cechToHModuleIso}
  Let $k$ be a field, $C : \Over\,(\Spec\,(\CommRingCat.\mathtt{of}\,k))$, $F$ a sheaf of $\ModuleCat\,k$, $\mathcal U : \iota \to \Opens\,C.\mathtt{left}.\mathtt{toTopCat}$. Assume $\HasExt_u$ on the sheaf category (single-universe; \emph{no} $\HasExt_{u+1}$ required, in contrast to iter-049 / iter-050 where the universe bridge demands both). Under $[\IsCechAcyclicCover\,F\,\mathcal U]$, $[\HasCechToHModuleIso\,F\,\mathcal U]$, and $n \geq 1$, the type $\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,(\bigsqcup_i \mathcal U_i)$ is a subsingleton.
\end{theorem}

\begin{proof}
\leanok
  Direct application of Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_prime_supr_of_isCechAcyclicCover} (iter-048's explicit-argument consumer) with the iter-050 extractor $\Scheme.\cechToHModuleIso$ supplied as the explicit $\mathtt{compIso}$ argument; the extractor fires automatically on the $[\HasCechToHModuleIso\,F\,\mathcal U]$ instance. Plan-agent $\mathtt{lean\_run\_code}$ probe (iter-051 pass) confirms the body $\mathtt{subsingleton\_HModule}'\_\mathtt{supr\_of\_isCechAcyclicCover}\,\cechToHModuleIso\,n\,h_n$ typechecks end-to-end with kernel-only axioms $[\propext, \Classical.\mathtt{choice}, \Quot.\mathtt{sound}]$.
\end{proof}

\begin{theorem}\leanok
[Instance-driven supremum HModule\texttt{'} consumer, curve form, iter-051]
  \label{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_prime_supr_of_hasCechToHModuleIso_curve}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.subsingleton_HModule'_supr_of_hasCechToHModuleIso_curve}
  \uses{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_prime_supr_of_hasCechToHModuleIso, def:Scheme_toModuleKSheaf}
  Curve specialisation at $F := \Scheme.\toModuleKSheaf\,C$ via the named-argument $(\mathcal U := \mathcal U)$ syntax.
\end{theorem}

\begin{proof}
\leanok
  Direct application of Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_subsingleton_HModule_prime_supr_of_hasCechToHModuleIso}. Plan-agent $\mathtt{lean\_run\_code}$ probe (iter-051 pass) confirms kernel-only axioms.
\end{proof}

\subsection{Toward the iter-052+ comparison theorem (informal scoping)}

Mathlib has $\mathtt{cechComplexFunctor}$ (\texttt{Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/SheafCohomology/Cech.lean}) but \emph{no} comparison theorem to derived-functor cohomology. The substantive iter-052+ obligation is to construct, for any sheaf $F$ on $C.\mathtt{left}$ and cover $\mathcal U$ with $[\IsCechAcyclicCover\,F\,\mathcal U]$ (\emph{or} a slightly weaker hypothesis), a natural $\LinearEquiv$
\[
  \mathrm{compIso}_n \,:\, \cechCohomology\,C\,F\,\mathcal U\,n \;\equiv_k\; \HModulePrime\,k\,F\,n\,\big(\bigsqcup_i \mathcal U_i\big), \qquad \forall n.
\]
The standard mathematical decomposition is the Čech-to-derived spectral sequence:
\[
  E_2^{p,q} \;=\; \check H^p\big(\mathcal U,\, \underline{H^q}(F)\big) \;\Longrightarrow\; H^{p+q}\big(\bigsqcup\mathcal U,\, F\big),
\]
which under the acyclicity hypothesis $\check H^q(\mathcal U_{i_0..i_p}, F) = 0$ for $q > 0$ collapses on the $E_2$ page to give $\check H^n \cong H^n$. Mathlib does not have the spectral-sequence machinery in the required form; the project-local construction is therefore expected via the dual chain-level route:
\begin{enumerate}
  \item View the sheafified-Yoneda-free $\Yoneda^{\mathrm{free}}_\bullet \,:\, n \mapsto (\mathtt{presheafToSheaf}).\mathrm{obj}\big((\mathtt{yoneda} \circ \free\,k).\mathrm{obj}\,(\mathcal U_{i_0\cap\cdots\cap i_n})\big)$ as a complex of sheaves whose homology in degree 0 is $(\mathtt{presheafToSheaf}).\mathrm{obj}\big((\mathtt{yoneda} \circ \free\,k).\mathrm{obj}\,(\bigsqcup\mathcal U)\big)$ (sheafification of the Čech sheaf-resolution of the free sheaf on $\bigsqcup\mathcal U$) and whose higher homologies vanish under acyclicity (the substantive computational step).
  \item Apply $\mathrm{Hom}(-, F)$ degree-wise, picking up $\Hom\big(\Yoneda^{\mathrm{free}}_n,\,F\big) \cong \prod_{i_0,\ldots,i_n} F(\mathcal U_{i_0\cap\cdots\cap i_n}) = (\cechCochain)_n$ on the LHS, and $\Hom\big((\mathtt{presheafToSheaf}).\mathrm{obj}\,(\mathtt{yoneda}\circ\free\,k).\mathrm{obj}\,(\bigsqcup\mathcal U),\, F\big) = \HModulePrime\,k\,F\,0\,(\bigsqcup\mathcal U)$ on the RHS at degree 0.
  \item Pass to cohomology and chain to $\Ext^n$ via the augmentation; under acyclicity the comparison is a quasi-iso, and the induced map on $\Ext^n$ gives the comparison.
\end{enumerate}
This decomposes into multiple iterations: (a) iter-052 constructs the Čech sheaf-resolution of the sheafified-Yoneda-free at degree $\geq 1$ (computational; the alternating face complex is exact under acyclicity); (b) iter-053+ chains via $\Ext$ functoriality. An alternative parallel branch is the basic-open cover acyclicity (Koszul-type alternating-sum exactness on localisations) which can proceed in parallel with the comparison construction. Estimate: 4--6 iterations, $\sim 200$--$400$ LOC.

